You are implementing a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/` using `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

## Project Structure
- **Server project:** `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/`
- **Client project:** `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/`
- This is Interactive Auto, Global mode — all interactive components go in the `.Client` project
- Identity auth is already configured with SQLite

## Architecture Rules (Auto mode)
- Interactive components MUST live in `.Client` project
- No direct DB access from `.Client` — use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there
- Implement server-side versions using EF Core in the server project
- Register matching services in BOTH Program.cs files
- Expose data through minimal API endpoints in server Program.cs

## What to Implement

### 1. Shipment Model (in `.Client` project since both sides need it)

Create `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:

```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime LastUpdated { get; set; }
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Delayed,
    Cancelled
}
```

### 2. Service Interface (in `.Client` project)

Create `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:

```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id);
    Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment);
    Task<Shipment> UpdateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment);
}
```

### 3. Client-side HTTP Implementation (in `.Client` project)

Create `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:

```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient httpClient) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.GetAsync($"api/shipments/track/{Uri.EscapeDataString(trackingNumber)}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.GetAsync($"api/shipments/{id}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>() ?? shipment;
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> UpdateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{shipment.Id}", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<Shipment>() ?? shipment;
    }
}
```

### 4. Server-side EF Implementation

First, update `ApplicationDbContext` at `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add a `Shipments` DbSet. Read the file first, then add `DbSet<ShipmentEntity>`.

Create `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/Data/ShipmentEntity.cs`:

```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class ShipmentEntity
{
    public int Id { get; set; }

    [Required, MaxLength(50)]
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required, MaxLength(200)]
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required, MaxLength(200)]
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public int Status { get; set; }

    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }

    [MaxLength(200)]
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [MaxLength(500)]
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public DateTime LastUpdated { get; set; }
}
```

Create `/tmp/sv-f3cd8f986b34414aa9063fe6b7f74c28/ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs`:

```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServerService(ApplicationDbContext db) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await db.Shipments
            .OrderByDescending(s => s.LastUpdated)
            .Select(s => ToModel(s))
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var entity = await db.Shipments.FirstOrDefaultAsync(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber);
        return entity is null ? null : ToModel(entity);
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        var entity = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        return entity is null ? null : ToModel(entity);
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> CreateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var entity = ToEntity(shipment);
        entity.CreatedAt = DateTime.UtcNow;
        entity.LastUpdated = DateTime.UtcNow;
        entity.TrackingNumber = GenerateTrackingNumber();
        db.Shipments.Add(entity);
        await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return ToModel(entity);
    }

    public async Task<Shipment> UpdateShipmentAsync(Shipment shipment)
    {
        var entity = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(shipment.Id)
            ?? throw new InvalidOperationException("Shipment not found");
        entity.Origin = shipment.Origin;
        entity.Destination = shipment.Destination;
        entity.Status = (int)shipment.Status;
        entity.EstimatedDelivery = shipment.EstimatedDelivery;
        entity.CustomerEmail = shipment.CustomerEmail;
        entity.Description = shipment.Description;
        entity.LastUpdated = DateTime.UtcNow;
        await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return ToModel(entity);
    }

    private static string GenerateTrackingNumber()
    {
        return $"SHP-{DateTime.UtcNow:yyyyMMdd}-{Random.Shared.Next(10000, 99999)}";
    }

    private static Shipment ToModel(ShipmentEntity e) => new()
    {
        Id = e.Id,
        TrackingNumber = e.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = e.Origin,
        Destination = e.Destination,
        Status = (ShipmentStatus)e.Status,
        EstimatedDelivery = e.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerEmail = e.CustomerEmail,
        Description = e.Description,
        CreatedAt = e.CreatedAt,
        LastUpdated = e.LastUpdated
    };

    private static ShipmentEntity ToEntity(Shipment s) => new()
    {
        Id = s.Id,
        TrackingNumber = s.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = s.Origin,
        Destination = s.Destination,
        Status = (int)s.Status,
        EstimatedDelivery = s.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerEmail = s.CustomerEmail,
        Description = s.Description,
        CreatedAt = s.CreatedAt,
        LastUpdated = s.LastUpdated
    };
}
```

### 5. API Endpoints and Service Registration

Edit the server `Program.cs` to add:
- `IShipmentService` registration (server-side implementation)
- Minimal API endpoints for shipments
- Database seeding with sample data

Add these registrations AFTER the existing service registrations (before `var app = builder.Build();`):

```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();
```

Add the needed usings at top:
```csharp
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
```

Add API endpoints AFTER `app.MapAdditionalIdentityEndpoints();` but BEFORE `app.Run();`:

```csharp
// Shipment API endpoints
var shipmentApi = app.MapGroup("api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

shipmentApi.MapGet("/", async (IShipmentService service) =>
    Results.Ok(await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync()));

